                  <msItem>
                     <p>

                        <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> the <surname>porter</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> grants to William his son, for his homage and service, (i) that manse in <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> which is between the manse of William de B—— on one side and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Braibroc</surname>
                        </persName> on the other; (ii) one a[cre] of land—½ an acre in the south field reaching to the Baddeby road, and ½ an acre in the north field, lying over ‘le Lome’. Rent: a pair of gloves worth ½d. at Easter, for all service saving the principal service pertaining to the manse: also he is to keep a lamp burning while mass is sung in the parish church of <placeName key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName> for the soul of the grantor, <persName>
                           <forename>Matilda</forename> his wife</persName>, &amp;c., 
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Gemme</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">fitz-Nigel</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> the <surname>porter</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">fitz-Nigel</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Neubold</surname>
                        </persName>,
   <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> the <surname>smith</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Jordan</forename> of <surname>Draitone</surname>
                        </persName>. [<hi rend="italic">Torn.</hi>]
   <origDate notBefore="1244" notAfter="1257">
                           <supplied>1244–57.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
